---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const webpageSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "@id": "https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation/#webpage",
  "url": "https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation",
  "name": "Enterprise AI Operating Model | Chandra Kanojia",
  "description": "A board-level view on enterprise AI, governed execution, human-agent workflow, CRM/Salesforce, platform reliability, and regulated operating outcomes.",
  "isPartOf": { "@id": "https://chandrakanojia.com/#website" },
  "about": { "@id": "https://chandrakanojia.com/#person" }
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://chandrakanojia.com" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Enterprise AI", "item": "https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation" }
  ]
};
---

<PageLayout
  title="Enterprise AI Operating Model | Governed Execution in Regulated Enterprises"
  description="A board-level view on enterprise AI, governed execution, human-agent workflow, CRM/Salesforce, platform reliability, and regulated operating outcomes."
  canonical="https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation"
  jsonLd={[webpageSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="enterprise-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Enterprise AI</p>
      <h1 id="enterprise-title">AI transformation is moving from assistance to execution.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Enterprise AI transformation is not a technology problem. It is an operating-model problem. The difference between programs that produce outcomes and programs that produce dashboards is execution discipline.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="mandate-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Agentic Enterprise Mandate</p>
      <h2 id="mandate-title">The next frontier is governed execution.</h2>
      <p>
        The next frontier will not be defined by how many copilots an enterprise deploys. It will be defined by how well the enterprise redesigns work so humans and agents can operate from the same context, permissions, workflows, controls, and outcome measures.
      </p>
      <p>
        The advantage is not model access. The advantage is converting enterprise knowledge, policy, data, and judgment into governed execution at scale: reducing cycle time, creating capacity, strengthening controls, improving customer experience, and accelerating revenue velocity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section muted" aria-labelledby="board-title">
    <div class="container narrow board-callout">
      <p class="eyebrow">For boards and executive teams</p>
      <h2 id="board-title">The enterprise AI question has changed.</h2>
      <p>
        The question is no longer whether the technology can produce capability. The board-level question is whether management can govern the investment, redesign the work, control the risk, protect trust, and convert AI spend into measurable operating advantage.
      </p>
      <p>
        That requires more than experimentation. It requires an operating model that can absorb AI.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="principles-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Operating principles</p>
        <h2 id="principles-title">Four rules that survive the demo stage.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid four">
        <article class="principle-card"><p>The flashy demo is autonomy. The durable product is controlled autonomy.</p></article>
        <article class="principle-card"><p>Long context is not memory. Evidence discipline is the control.</p></article>
        <article class="principle-card"><p>Benchmarks are not work. Work has politics, risk, format, approval, and cleanup cost.</p></article>
        <article class="principle-card"><p>The next moat is not prompt engineering. It is workflow ownership.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section" aria-labelledby="enterprise-cta-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2 id="enterprise-cta-title">Enterprise AI mandates require operating proof.</h2>
      <p>For regulated-institution scale, the work has to connect strategy, governance, platforms, workflow, adoption, and measurable outcomes.</p>
      <a class="button primary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chandra-kanojia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
